shippingstore

Class Transaction

  • java.lang.Object
    • shippingstore.Transaction
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable

    public class Transaction
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable
    This class is a very simple representation of a transaction. There are only getter methods and no setter methods and as a result a transaction cannot be mutated once initialized.
    See Also:

    • Constructor Detail

      • Transaction

        public Transaction(java.lang.Integer customerID,
                   java.lang.String trackingNumber,
                   java.util.Date shippingDate,
                   java.util.Date deliverDate,
                   java.lang.Float cost,
                   java.lang.Integer employeeID)
        This constructor initializes the transaction object. The constructor provides no user input validation. That should be handled by the class that creates a user object.
        Parameters:
        customerID - an Integer that represents the ID # of the customer who ordered the transaction
        trackingNumber - a String that represents the tracking number of the package in the transaction.
        shippingDate - a Date that represents the day the package was sent
        deliverDate - a Date that represents the day the package was received
        cost - a Float that represents the cost of the transaction
        employeeID - a Integer that represents the ID of the employee who completed the transaction
